<title>FRANCE: Saint-Gobain to spread activity worldwide - chairman.</title>
<headline>Saint-Gobain to spread activity worldwide - chairman.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1996-11-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>- Saint-Gobain glassmaking group is seeking to strengthen its market penetration in Asia and the United States, chairman Jean-Louis Beffa said in an interview with daily Le Figaro.</p>
<p>&quot;Our ambition is to give our group a better geographic coverage to make it less dependent on economic cycles,&quot; Beffa says.</p>
<p>He said this implies a ten-year project to spread activities across four areas: France, the rest of Europe, the United States, and Asia and Latin America, mainly for glass.</p>
<p>In the United States, Saint-Gobain just bought all of Ball Foster Glass, and is making an offer for Anchor Glass.</p>
<p>-- Paris Newsroom 331 4221 5452.</p>
